Prefix + HashMap Notes:

## 🔥 Updated Prefix Sum + HashMap Summary Table

| Question Type                          | Map Initialize   | Map me kya check karte hain                  | Map me kya store karte hain |
| -------------------------------------- | ---------------- | -------------------------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| **Count subarrays with sum = k**       | `map.put(0, 1)`  | `sum - k` exist hai ya nahi                  | `sum → frequency`           |
| **Longest subarray with sum = k**      | `map.put(0, -1)` | `sum - k` exist hai ya nahi                  | `sum → first index`         |
| **Equal 0s and 1s (longest)**          | `map.put(0, -1)` | same `sum` exist hai ya nahi                 | `sum → first index`         |
| **Count subarrays with equal 0s & 1s** | `map.put(0, 1)`  | same `sum` exist hai ya nahi                 | `sum → frequency`           |
| **Longest subarray divisible by k**    | `map.put(0, -1)` | same `remainder (sum % k)` exist hai ya nahi | `remainder → first index`   |
| **Count subarrays divisible by k**     | `map.put(0, 1)`  | same `remainder (sum % k)` exist hai ya nahi | `remainder → frequency`     |

---

## 🧠 Final Clear Pattern (Ultimate 🔥)

| Type            | Store     | Check                   |
| --------------- | --------- | ----------------------- |
| **Count**       | frequency | match (sum / remainder) |
| **Length**      | index     | match (sum / remainder) |
| **Exact k**     | `sum - k` |                         |
| **Divisible k** | `sum % k` |                         |

---

## ⚡ One-line Ultimate Memory Trick

👉
**"Count → frequency, Length → index, Exact → (sum-k), Divisible → remainder"**
---

Modulo wala case
Always use:
rem = (sum % k + k) % k;


First occurrence rule
Length wale questions me:
if(!map.containsKey(...)) store karo
