Prefix sum without HashMap:-

## 🔥 Prefix Sum (Without HashMap) Summary Table

| Question Type                | Initialization       | Preprocessing                      | Query / Logic                                     | Store kya karte hain  |
| ---------------------------- | -------------------- | ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- | --------------------- |
| **Basic Prefix Sum Build**   | `prefix[0] = arr[0]` | `prefix[i] = prefix[i-1] + arr[i]` | —                                                 | prefix array          |
| **Range Sum Query (L to R)** | prefix array ready   | —                                  | `prefix[r] - prefix[l-1]`                         | prefix array          |
| **Range Sum (L = 0 case)**   | —                    | —                                  | `prefix[r]`                                       | prefix array          |
| **Total Sum of Array**       | —                    | —                                  | `prefix[n-1]`                                     | prefix array          |
| **Equilibrium Index**        | total sum nikal lo   | —                                  | left sum = right sum                              | prefix ya running sum |
| **Left Sum / Right Sum**     | —                    | —                                  | left = `prefix[i-1]`, right = `total - prefix[i]` | prefix array          |

---

## 🧠 Key Concepts

### 1️ Prefix Array ka matlab

```java
prefix[i] = 0 se i tak ka sum
```

---

### 2️ Range Query Formula

```java
sum(l, r) = prefix[r] - prefix[l-1]
```

---

### 3️ Edge Case

```java
if(l == 0) → directly prefix[r]
```

---

### 4️ Kab use hota hai?

* Multiple queries (Q zyada ho)
* Static array (update nahi ho raha)

---

## ⚡ Prefix vs Prefix + HashMap (Final Clarity)

| Feature        | Prefix Only       | Prefix + HashMap                   |
| -------------- | ----------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Use case       | Range sum queries | Pattern detection                  |
| Query type     | fixed (L, R)      | dynamic (sum = k, divisible, etc.) |
| Data structure | array             | hashmap                            |
| Complexity     | O(1) per query    | O(N) overall                       |

---

## 🔥 One-line Memory Trick

👉
**"Prefix → fast range sum, HashMap → pattern detect"**
